                                                                                          Push notifications

                                                                                          Push notifications are short messages sent from an application to a user’s device, even when the user isn’t currently using an Uber app. Pushes can appear on the lock screen, in the notification center on the home screen, or in a banner at the top of whichever screen the user is engaged with.

                                                                                          Pushes help users accomplish their goals with ease and surface time-sensitive information about rides and orders, for example, when the user needs it.  


                                                                                          TL;DR

                                                                                          • A push notification should communicate the critical information the user needs right now and provide a way to take action

                                                                                          • Character counts are highly restricted due to localization:

                                                                                            • Header: 25

                                                                                            • Body: Aim for fewer than 40 characters, but don't exceed 100

                                                                                          • Interactive or visual elements should complement the content but not be necessary to convey its intended meaning

                                                                                          • It’s OK to use emojis to suggest tone or emotion, but the message should make sense without them

                                                                                          • Action buttons are calls to action that allow users to respond to notifications quickly without opening the app 

                                                                                            • Use up to 3 buttons of up to 10 characters each

                                                                                          Anatomy of a push

                                                                                          All push notifications must be written for display on both Android and iOS (these platforms have different specifications).

                                                                                          • Follow the golden rule for localization: This states that you should leave enough room for the English text to expand up to 30% in other languages or up to 200% if the English text is fewer than 10 characters

                                                                                          • Always err on the side of brevity: Character count limits are only an approximation for available pixel width, and some characters are wider than others


                                                                                          Below are the specs that ensure that our pushes work on every device.

                                                                                          Component

                                                                                          Specs

                                                                                          App icon

                                                                                          Default small icon (can’t be changed)

                                                                                          Rich media

                                                                                          Recommended:

                                                                                          2:1 aspect ratio, landscape


                                                                                          Common sizes:

                                                                                          512 x 256 pixels

                                                                                          1440 x 720 pixels


                                                                                          Max width: 2,000 pixels

                                                                                          Min width: 300 pixels

                                                                                          Title

                                                                                          English: 19–25 characters

                                                                                          Translated: 40–50 characters


                                                                                          Titles of more than 25 characters may be truncated. Therefore, it’s good practice to frontload the title with the most critical information.

                                                                                          Time stamp

                                                                                          When the message was received (autogenerated)

                                                                                          Message

                                                                                          English: 30–40 characters, but no more than 100 Translated: 150 characters

                                                                                          Action buttons

                                                                                          English: Up to 3; 20 characters each

                                                                                          Translated: 30 characters each

                                                                                          Writing guidelines

                                                                                          Push notifications should answer these 3 questions:

                                                                                          • What does the user need to know right now? (Your driver is here)

                                                                                          • Why should the user care? (Your driver will wait 2 min)

                                                                                          • How should the user take action? (Please meet your driver at your pickup spot) 

                                                                                          Header (required)

                                                                                          • Headers must be succinct and enticing. They should either provide all the key information or entice the reader to engage with the body text to get a full understanding.

                                                                                          Do

                                                                                          Your driver is arriving

                                                                                          Rate your trip

                                                                                          Need a faster pickup?

                                                                                          Body (required)

                                                                                          • Avoid repeating words or concepts from the header in the body.

                                                                                          • Put critical contextual information in the first 30–40 characters of the body.

                                                                                          Do

                                                                                          After arriving, they’ll wait 2 min before leaving

                                                                                          Thanks for riding with [driver name]! Please rate your trip

                                                                                          Boost your offer amount to attract more drivers and get where you’re going faster

                                                                                           Action button (optional)

                                                                                          • When there’s an action the user can take, use action buttons so the user can respond immediately without opening the app. Use clear, short CTAs.

                                                                                          Do

                                                                                          Leave on // Turn off

                                                                                          Ride now

                                                                                          Tip // Send message

                                                                                          Style considerations

                                                                                          Personalization

                                                                                          Personalizing a push notification can increase its effectiveness.

                                                                                          • Address users by name when possible

                                                                                          John, you’ve accomplished a lot today. Treat yourself with 30% off.

                                                                                          • Include information like hometown and other local specifics when it makes sense

                                                                                          Punctuation

                                                                                          • Skip the periods in headers and single-sentence pushes, but do use periods in the body if you have two or more short sentences 

                                                                                          • Use exclamation points sparingly, as they can make it seem like you’re shouting

                                                                                          Variables

                                                                                          Avoid variables if you can, but if you need to use a name or other variable in the notification, remember to account for the maximum possible character count of the variable in question

                                                                                          Emojis

                                                                                          It's OK to use a single emoji in a push notification. Make sure to follow the guidance in Emojis to avoid pitfalls.

                                                                                          • Include an emoji only at the end of a message, and put it outside any punctuation

                                                                                          • The message should make sense without the emoji


                                                                                          Localization

                                                                                          Add a note for engineering, instructing them to include the maximum character limit in the Rosetta Key Description to give the translators some guardrails.                                                                                           Related resources

                                                                                          Our agreements with our mobile OS partners (Apple, Google), our industry regulators, and the tools we use to manage notifications all impose rules on how and when we send notifications to customers. Learn the rules before composing your notifications.
